race.comment: ANDI DON'T CARE (8) is unlucky to still be a maiden placing at her past three starts and strikes a very winnable contest here. Gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination and should be going very close to shedding the maiden tag. BOOM BREAK (2) resumes here but has hit the top-four in all four starts to date and has revved up for this with a recent trial. Will prove tough to hold out. Former Victorian ZEAMAIZE (5) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what he faced down south. Respect any push in betting. ZALIQUE (7) is facing the starter for the first time but has shown ability at the trials and is sure to be well-educated out of the Dunn yard. Gets 3kg off with the claim and can run a big race on debut. MR STORMY (4) rounds out the selections.
